Now,
*Firstly, we have a regular 52 card deck.
As there are 4 suits in it, therefore, the probability of getting one hearts from a 52-card deck is
</ think>
<answer>
\begin{align}
P &= \frac{13}{52} &&\text{as there are 13 hearts in a deck of cards} \\
&= \frac{1}{4}
\end{align}
*On the second card, we have to find the probability of getting a 10.
There are 4 tens in a 52-card deck.
P = \frac{4}{51}
</ answer>
As the events are simultaneous, the answer will be multiplied.
Therefore, the probability = \frac{1}{4} \times \frac{4}{51} = \frac{1}{51}
</ answer>

